! for regular keys, we can simply set their keycodes to what we like. 
! for modifier keys, however, there is a modifier map that needs to 
! be updated. The add Control = Control_L searches through all keys, 
! sees which have the specified modifier keysym, and adds that keycode to the modifier. 
! In this way, the modifier map is behind whenever we change a keycode and needs to be updated.
!
!
keycode 66 = Control_L

clear Lock
remove Control = Control_L
add Control = Control_L

